title.narrative: 5.7 WASH:OUTCOME 5: PROGRAMME EXCELLENCE

description.narrative: UNICEF EAPR has strengthened capacity to design and implement gender responsive, equity focused Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) programmes that deliver results for the most disadvantaged children at scale., which contributes to Disaster Risk Reduction, Environmental Sustainability, Sanitation, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: COs practice programming excellence to achieve quality results for children at scale in both development and humanitarian settings

title.narrative: UNICEF EAPR has strengthened capacity to design and implement gender responsive, equity focused WASH programmes that deliverresults for the most disadvantaged children at scale.

description.narrative: Across the region, UNICEF supported national capacities to design, implement and monitor equity-focused WASH programmes. WASH was critical to support the COVID-19 response in the region, focusing on hand hygiene, infection prevention and control, and support to schools and healthcare facilities, building momentum to sustain gains in service in the transition to the recovery phase. Working with the private sector and young people, innovations were identified and deployed to support service provision, in the response and beyond. | Status:Met | As-of Date:28/03/2022
